@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Selling Mobile Phones to Agent";
    ViewBag.Message = "Information about selling mobile phones to an agent";
}
<main aria-labelledby="title">
    <h2 id="title">@ViewBag.Title</h2>
    <h3>@ViewBag.Message</h3>

    <p>When selling mobile phones to agents, it is important to consider the following:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Product Selection: Choose a range of popular and high-quality mobile phones to offer to the agents. Consider factors such as brand reputation, features, and price range to cater to a diverse customer base.</li>
        <li>Pricing Strategy: Set competitive prices for the mobile phones that provide value for both the agent and end customers. Consider offering bulk discounts or incentives for agents who achieve sales targets.</li>
        <li>Inventory Management: Ensure proper inventory management to meet the demand from agents. Keep track of stock levels, reorder points, and lead times to avoid stockouts and fulfill orders promptly.</li>
        <li>Marketing Support: Provide marketing materials and support to agents to help them promote and sell the mobile phones effectively. This can include product brochures, advertising materials, and online marketing campaigns.</li>
        <li>Sales Training: Conduct training sessions or provide resources to educate agents about the features and benefits of the mobile phones. This will enable them to effectively communicate with potential customers and address their queries.</li>
        <li>After-Sales Service: Establish a system for handling customer inquiries, repairs, and warranty claims. Ensure agents have access to necessary resources and processes to provide satisfactory after-sales support.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>By following these guidelines, you can build a successful relationship with agents and effectively sell mobile phones to a wider customer base.</p>
</main>
